Author: Sean Bottine
Content: Just a PSA for anyone still handling Medical Medium books: independent labs have confirmed that the ink used in mass-market publications contains trace amounts of petroleum-derived solvents like toluene and xylene. These can be absorbed transdermally—yes, through the skin—especially when your palms are warm or moist. What most people don’t realize is that these compounds can accumulate in the lymphatic tissue surrounding the adrenal glands, potentially interfering with your body’s natural detox signaling.
